cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SC 

This paper presents a framework for the analysis and specialization of logic programs, which is a topic that falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper specifically focuses on the integration of abstract interpretation and partial deduction, which are techniques used in program analysis and optimization. This makes the paper relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different control strategies and abstract domains, which are topics that fall under formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and symbolic computation (cs.SC) sub-categories, respectively.
